            <div class="allset-page-heading"><h1>Reference:HSK Standard Course 1</h1></div>
            <!-- subtitle -->
            <div id="contentSub" ></div>
            <!-- /subtitle -->
                        <div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="mw-parser-output"><p><span class="plainlinks"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://amzn.to/2G1xjf5"><img width="300" class="alignright link-amazon" src="https&#58;//images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/I/41EtPyPqDAL._SX365_BO1,204,203,200_.jpg" /></a></span>
<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://amzn.to/2G1xjf5">HSK Standard Course 1</a>, by Liu Chang and Lu Jiang, contains 15 lessons. Authorized by Hanban, HSK Standard Course is developed under the joint efforts of Beijing Language and Culture University Press and Chinese Testing International (CTI). With HSK test papers as its primary source, HSK Standard Course is characterized by a humorous style, familiar topics and a scientific course design.
</p><p>You may also want to refer to our full list of <a href="HSK_1_grammar_points" title="HSK 1 grammar points">HSK 1 grammar points</a>.
</p>
<div id="toc" class="toc"><input type="checkbox" role="button" id="toctogglecheckbox" class="toctogglecheckbox" style="display:none" /><div class="toctitle" lang="en" dir="ltr"><h2>Contents</h2><span class="toctogglespan"><label class="toctogglelabel" for="toctogglecheckbox"></label></span></div>
<ul>
<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-1"><a href="./Reference:HSK_Standard_Course_1#Grammar_Points_by_Table_of_Contents"><span class="tocnumber">1</span> <span class="toctext">Grammar Points by Table of Contents</span></a></li>
<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-2"><a href="./Reference:HSK_Standard_Course_1#Grammar_Point_References_to_This_Book"><span class="tocnumber">2</span> <span class="toctext">Grammar Point References to This Book</span></a></li>
<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-3"><a href="./Reference:HSK_Standard_Course_1#HSK_Standard_Course_.28HSK_.E6.A0.87.E5.87.86.E6.95.99.E7.A8.8B.29"><span class="tocnumber">3</span> <span class="toctext">HSK Standard Course (HSK 标准教程)</span></a></li>
<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-4"><a href="./Reference:HSK_Standard_Course_1#See_also"><span class="tocnumber">4</span> <span class="toctext">See also</span></a></li>
</ul>
</div>

<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Grammar_Points_by_Table_of_Contents">Grammar Points by Table of Contents</span></h2>
<ol><li>Lesson 1: 你好 Hello</li>
<li>Lesson 2: 谢谢你 Thank you</li>
<li>Lesson 3: 你叫什么名字 What's your name
<ol><li><a href="Placement_of_question_words" title="Placement of question words">疑问代词“什么” The Interrogative Pronoun "什么"</a></li>
<li><a href="Connecting_nouns_with_&quot;shi&quot;" title="Connecting nouns with &quot;shi&quot;">“是”字句 The "是" Sentence</a></li>
<li><a href="Yes-no_questions_with_&quot;ma&quot;" title="Yes-no questions with &quot;ma&quot;">用“吗”的疑问句 Interrogative Sentences with "吗"</a></li></ol></li>
<li>Lesson 4: 她是我的汉语老师 She is my Chinese teacher
<ol><li><a href="Placement_of_question_words" title="Placement of question words">疑问代词“谁”、“哪” The Interrogative Pronouns “谁” and “哪”</a></li>
<li><a href="Expressing_possession_with_&quot;de&quot;" title="Expressing possession with &quot;de&quot;">结构助词“的” The Structural Particle “的”</a> (see also <a href="Expressing_close_possession_without_&quot;de&quot;" title="Expressing close possession without &quot;de&quot;">Expressing close possession without "de"</a>)</li>
<li><a href="Questions_with_&quot;ne&quot;" title="Questions with &quot;ne&quot;">疑问助词“呢” (1) The Interrogative Particle “呢” (1)</a></li></ol></li>
<li>Lesson 5: 她女儿今年二十岁 Her daughter is 20 years old this year
<ol><li><a href="Measure_words_in_quantity_questions" title="Measure words in quantity questions">疑问代词“几” The Interrogative Pronouns “几”</a> (see also <a href="Age_with_&quot;sui&quot;" title="Age with &quot;sui&quot;">Age with "sui"</a>)</li>
<li><a href="Structure_of_numbers" title="Structure of numbers">百以内的数字 Numbers below 100</a></li>
<li><a href="Change_of_state_with_&quot;le&quot;" title="Change of state with &quot;le&quot;">“了”表变化  “了” Indicating a Change</a></li>
<li><a href="Asking_about_degree_with_&quot;duo&quot;" title="Asking about degree with &quot;duo&quot;">“多 + 大”表示疑问 The Interrogative Phrase “多 + 大”</a></li></ol></li>
<li>Lesson 6: 我会说汉语 I can speak Chinese
<ol><li><a href="Expressing_a_learned_skill_with_&quot;hui&quot;" title="Expressing a learned skill with &quot;hui&quot;">能愿动词“会” (1) The Modal Verb “会” (1)</a></li>
<li><a href="Simple_&quot;noun_+_adjective&quot;_sentences" title="Simple &quot;noun + adjective&quot; sentences">形容词谓语句 Sentences with an Adjectival Predicate</a></li>
<li><a href="How_to_do_something_with_&quot;zenme&quot;" title="How to do something with &quot;zenme&quot;">疑问代词“怎么” (1) The Interrogative Pronoun “怎么” (1)</a></li></ol></li>
<li>Lesson 7: 今天几号 What's the date today
<ol><li><a href="Structure_of_dates" title="Structure of dates">日期的表达 (1)：月、日 / 号、星期 Expression of Date (1): month, date, day of the week</a> (see also <a href="Structure_of_days_of_the_week" title="Structure of days of the week">Structure of days of the week</a>)</li>
<li><a href="Nominal_predicate_sentence" title="Nominal predicate sentence">名词谓语句 Sentences with a Nominal Predicate</a> ...........</li>
<li><a href="Using_the_verb_&quot;qu&quot;" title="Using the verb &quot;qu&quot;">连动词 (1) ：去 + 地方 + 做什么 Sentences with a Serial Verb Construction (1) ：去 + place + to do sth. </a></li></ol></li>
<li>Lesson 8: 我想喝茶 I'd like some tea
<ol><li><a href="Expressing_&quot;would_like_to&quot;_with_&quot;xiang&quot;" title="Expressing &quot;would like to&quot; with &quot;xiang&quot;">能愿动词“想” The Modal Verb “想”</a></li>
<li><a href="Measure_words_in_quantity_questions" title="Measure words in quantity questions">疑问代词“多少” The Interrogative Pronoun “多少”</a></li>
<li><a href="Measure_word_&quot;ge&quot;" title="Measure word &quot;ge&quot;">量词“个”、“口” The Measure Words “个” and “口”</a></li>
<li><a href="Counting_money" title="Counting money">钱数的表达 Expression of the Amount of Money</a></li></ol></li>
<li>Lesson 9: 你儿子在哪儿工作 Where does your son work
<ol><li><a href="Expressing_existence_in_a_place_with_&quot;zai&quot;" title="Expressing existence in a place with &quot;zai&quot;">动词“在” The Verb “在”</a></li>
<li><a href="Placement_of_question_words" title="Placement of question words">疑问代词“哪儿” The Interrogative Pronoun “哪儿”</a></li>
<li><a href="Indicating_location_with_&quot;zai&quot;_before_verbs" title="Indicating location with &quot;zai&quot; before verbs">介词“在” The Preposition “在”</a></li>
<li><a href="Questions_with_&quot;ne&quot;" title="Questions with &quot;ne&quot;">疑问助词“呢” (2) The Interrogative Particle “呢” (2) </a></li></ol></li>
<li>Lesson 10: 我能坐这儿吗 Can I sit here
<ol><li><a href="Expressing_existence_with_&quot;you&quot;" title="Expressing existence with &quot;you&quot;">“有”字句表示存在 The “有” Sentence: Indicating Existence</a></li>
<li><a href="Expressing_&quot;and&quot;_with_&quot;he&quot;" title="Expressing &quot;and&quot; with &quot;he&quot;">连词“和” The Conjunction “和”</a></li>
<li><a href="Expressing_ability_or_possibility_with_&quot;neng&quot;" title="Expressing ability or possibility with &quot;neng&quot;">能愿动词“能” The Modal Verb "能"</a></li>
